WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified body profile for the Canon EOS C700 cinema camera. It contains
the exact mathematical IDT (Input Device Transform), Canon Log 2 and Canon
Log 3 curve parameters with their inverses, native color space primaries for
Cinema Gamut and Rec.2020, white balance presets, ISO sensitivity ranges, and
the Dual Gain Output (DGO) sensor model. This is the single source of truth
for linearizing C700 footage to scene-referred ACES2065-1.

WHY IT EXISTS
Canon’s Cinema RAW Light format encodes up to 15 stops of dynamic range using
Canon Log 2 (maximum range) or Canon Log 3 (balance of range and grading ease).
The camera offers both Cinema Gamut and Rec.2020 color spaces. To integrate
C700 footage into an ACES or GIOP pipeline, every pixel must be exactly
linearized. Without this certified body file, the DGO sensor’s unique
dual-gain behavior cannot be correctly modelled, leading to highlight or
shadow errors in compositing.

HOW IT WORKS
The file defines the transform chain:
  1. Inverse Canon Log (2 or 3, depending on metadata) → linear RGB in
     the selected gamut (Cinema Gamut or Rec.2020).
  2. Selected gamut to ACES2065-1 matrix (3x3 certified).
  3. White balance gain inverse (as-shot or preset).
  4. DGO mode metadata handling (the sensor uses two simultaneous readouts
     with different gains; the RAW decoder combines them, and the IDT
     operates on the already-combined linear signal).
All constants are provided for both log curves and both gamuts.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- DaVinci Resolve (via DCTL or OCIO config)
- Nuke (via Python API or STMap)
- Baselight (BLG stack)
- Unreal Engine (virtual production)
- Any ACES‑compliant grading or compositing tool.

