5. ISO AND DGO (DUAL GAIN OUTPUT)
  The C700 uses a Dual Gain Output (DGO) sensor architecture, where each
  photodiode feeds two amplifiers with different gains simultaneously.
  The two readouts are combined in-camera to extend dynamic range.

  Base ISO:       800
  Effective EI range: 160–6400 (Canon Log 2), 160–12800 (Canon Log 3)
  Read noise (combined DGO): approximately 1.2 e⁻ (at base)
  Full well capacity: approximately 38,000 e⁻
  Dynamic range (SNR=1): 15 stops (Canon Log 2)

  The IDT is ISO‑agnostic; the same inverse log and matrix apply
  regardless of ISO setting. ISO metadata is used only for noise
  profiling. The DGO combination is performed in the RAW decoder before
  the IDT, so the IDT receives a single linear signal.

6. METADATA HANDLING
  Canon Cinema RAW Light clips carry:
    - Active log curve (Canon Log 2 / Canon Log 3)
    - Active color space (Cinema Gamut / Rec.2020)
    - ISO setting
    - White balance (Kelvin + tint)
    - Lens data (EF mount metadata)
  The GIOP IDT reads these values at runtime. If metadata is absent,
  the IDT defaults to Canon Log 2, Cinema Gamut, ISO 800, and Daylight.

